name: exp_log_ops
jaxpr:
{ lambda ; a:f32[4]. let
    b:f32[4] = exp a
    c:f32[4] = abs a
    d:f32[4] = add c 1.0:f32[]
    e:f32[4] = log d
    f:f32[4] = add b e
    g:f32[4] = abs a
    h:f32[4] = sqrt g
    i:f32[4] = add f h
  in (i,) }
hlo:
module @jit_exp_log_ops attributes {mhlo.num_partitions = 1 : i32, mhlo.num_replicas = 1 : i32} {
  func.func public @main(%arg0: tensor<4xf32>) -> (tensor<4xf32> {jax.result_info = "result"}) {
    %0 = stablehlo.exponential %arg0 : tensor<4xf32>
    %1 = stablehlo.abs %arg0 : tensor<4xf32>
    %cst = stablehlo.constant dense<1.000000e+00> : tensor<f32>
    %2 = stablehlo.broadcast_in_dim %cst, dims = [] : (tensor<f32>) -> tensor<4xf32>
    %3 = stablehlo.add %1, %2 : tensor<4xf32>
    %4 = stablehlo.log %3 : tensor<4xf32>
    %5 = stablehlo.add %0, %4 : tensor<4xf32>
    %6 = stablehlo.abs %arg0 : tensor<4xf32>
    %7 = stablehlo.sqrt %6 : tensor<4xf32>
    %8 = stablehlo.add %5, %7 : tensor<4xf32>
    return %8 : tensor<4xf32>
  }
}
